## Evidence Notes

- Existing selected-profile surfaces were already materially present:
  - selected profile summary, data contract labels, and track statuses in workflow agent views
  - selected profile-aware provider command in provider support
  - profile-aware bootstrap inputs
- The concrete bugs closed in this slice were:
  - unselected machine surfaces hid opt-in profile discovery entirely
  - selected bootstrap commands degraded back to generic `provider-status` / `workflow-status`
  - selected first-run bootstrap routing degraded back to profile-less `workflow-status --phase bootstrap`
  - selected evidence-review and auto-quant helper routes degraded back to profile-less `workflow-status` follow-ups
  - generic downstream `workflow-status` / `provider-status` follow-up strings could stay profile-less unless upgraded at the central workflow surface
  - factor-research / factor-autoresearch entry into the Auto-Quant handoff path had no provider-profile selector to carry forward
  - selected first-run `factors/backtest=` route still degraded back to a profile-less `factor-research` command until direct CLI verification caught it
  - selected human deferred `ask-user -> then factor-research` follow-ups could still degrade back to a profile-less command

## Success Standard For This Board

- Zero-config public default remains the default.
- Personal lane remains opt-in and hot-pluggable.
- Machine consumers can discover the optional personal lane without already being inside it.
- Once inside that lane, follow-up commands keep carrying the profile automatically.
